  <developer id="net.armatik">
    <name>Semen (Armatik) Fomchenkov</name>
  </developer>

  <content_rating type="oars-1.1">
    <content_attribute id="violence-cartoon">moderate</content_attribute>
    <content_attribute id="violence-fantasy">moderate</content_attribute>
    <content_attribute id="language-profanity">mild</content_attribute>
  </content_rating>

  <requires>
    <display_length compare="ge">360</display_length>
  </requires>
  <recommends>
    <control>pointing</control>
    <control>keyboard</control>
    <control>touch</control>
  </recommends>
  <supports>
    <internet>always</internet>
  </supports>

  <releases>
    <release version="0.8.5" date="2026-03-26">
      <description>
        <p>Removed light theme screenshot variants — AppStream does not support grouping by color scheme, so only dark theme screenshots are kept for a cleaner app listing.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.8.4" date="2026-03-21">
      <description>
        <p>Home button on nested navigation pages — quickly return to the main screen from deep release, genre, franchise or tag drill-downs. Hidden on the first level where back already leads home.</p>
        <p>Fixed bottom bar overlapping the last card in mobile layout. Genres and franchises now show an end-of-list indicator after all items load.</p>
        <p>Card labels clamped to 252px and the grid wrapped in Adw.Clamp(1600) so titles stay close to posters on wide screens.</p>
        <p>Smoother release page transitions — heavy widget construction deferred to the shown signal instead of blocking during the animation. Accent color extraction moved to idle callback. Loading spinner fills the viewport until episodes appear, preventing poster resize jumps.</p>
        <p>Added 23 screenshots to metainfo covering all views in light and dark themes, desktop and mobile layouts.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.8.3" date="2026-03-18">
      <description>
        <p>Added Russian content notice to description and keywords to metainfo. Clarified in README that API content is in Russian.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.8.2" date="2026-03-18">
      <description>
        <p>Preparing for Flathub publication. Added English README and separate Russian translation for multilingual repository support. Fixed minimum dependency versions in documentation (Libadwaita >= 1.6, GStreamer >= 1.24). Fixed translate URL in metainfo pointing to wrong branch.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.8.1" date="2026-03-17">
      <description>
        <p>Fixed release page not loading content — deferred initialization via GLib.idle_add was cancelled by NavigationView internal map/unmap cycle during push animation. Now uses the showing signal which fires after the transition completes.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.8.0" date="2026-03-17">
      <description>
        <p>Search dialog — full-featured search with category tabs (anime, genres, franchises, tags), animated scroll tracking, smart tag filtering, ongoing release refresh, episode progress display, and configurable category order. Keyboard navigation with Escape to close and category tab click-to-scroll.</p>
        <p>Redesigned preferences — blur unwatched episodes toggle, search category ordering with drag-and-drop, storage page reorganized into Cache and User Data groups with inline clear buttons. All reorderable lists use GNOME-style drag handles.</p>
        <p>Watch progress improvements — 90%% watched threshold marks episodes as completed across the app (release page, search dialog, progress bars, checkmarks). Near-end detection replaces fixed-seconds threshold.</p>
        <p>Smooth animations — release page content loads after push animation via deferred initialization, eliminating the stutter in the last pixels of navigation transitions.</p>
        <p>Accessibility and polish — player buttons have tooltips for screen readers, tag color circles use theme-safe borders for light and dark themes, episode separators adapt to current theme, GSettings enum keys validated with choices.</p>
        <p>Reliability — async API callbacks guarded against destroyed widgets, HTTP 4xx errors no longer degrade the client to offline mode, scroll animation timers properly cleaned up on dialog close, pycairo dependency validated at build time.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.7.1" date="2026-03-13">
      <description>
        <p>Fixed video player not starting — NavigationView internally maps and unmaps pages during push transitions, which caused the playback idle source to be cancelled before it could fire.</p>
        <p>Fixed catalog and other views showing infinite spinners on first launch — the same map/unmap cycle was aborting in-flight API requests and clearing pending data.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.7.0" date="2026-03-12">
      <description>
        <p>Configurable navigation — rearrange, show or hide tabs in the sidebar and bottom bar. First 3 tabs are shown as buttons, overflow tabs open in a BottomSheet with drag handle. Changes apply live without restart. Grid and list display styles for the sheet.</p>
        <p>Stability fixes — idle source tracking and cleanup on view unmap prevents use-after-free crashes, GStreamer bus signal handlers are properly disconnected on player cleanup, API callbacks are always invoked even in offline error paths, and duplicate GLib.source_remove calls have been eliminated.</p>
        <p>Code quality — release detail page decomposed into focused helper modules (episodes, related releases, tags), genre and franchise views unified under a shared base class, storage modules consolidated with shared atomic write, and widget-level tests added for views and widgets.</p>
        <p>Visual polish — adaptive tag pills switch between full and compact mode based on available space, SVG icon replaces text plus on tag badges, double hover background on sheet grid items removed, native BottomSheet animation with custom drag handle pills.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.6.1" date="2026-03-11">
      <description>
        <p>Bugfix: renamed action icons with app_id prefix (net.armatik.Kitsune.*) to prevent file conflicts with other applications when installed to the shared icon directory.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.6.0" date="2026-03-11">
      <description>
        <p>Tags and favorites — a new system for organizing your library. Create custom tags with emoji or colored icons, assign them to any release via the star button on the release page, and browse tagged collections in the new "Favorites &amp; Tags" tab. Tags are displayed as compact badges on catalog cards and as interactive pills on release pages. The tag creation dialog features an Adw.ToggleGroup switcher between emoji and color modes with inline icon chooser, color ring picker, duplicate name validation, and auto-generated names for color tags. Tag view supports both card grid and list modes with persistent mode preference. Tags can be deleted from the header bar or list view with a confirmation dialog, and changes propagate instantly to all visible cards.</p>
        <p>Episode watch progress tracking — progress bars appear on episode cards and list rows showing how much of each episode has been watched. Completed episodes are marked with an accent-colored checkmark. Unwatched episode previews can be blurred (configurable in preferences). Episodes can be filtered by watched/unwatched status using toggle buttons. Preview images show a loading spinner while loading and a placeholder icon when unavailable. Progress is refreshed automatically when returning from the player.</p>
        <p>Redesigned filter panel — the filter dialog has been replaced with a sliding side panel (OverlaySplitView) that overlays the entire window. Filters auto-apply with a 1-second debounce, genres and year ranges update asynchronously, and redundant catalog reloads on unchanged filters are suppressed.</p>
        <p>Genre navigation from release pages — clicking a genre chip on a release page now opens that genre's releases as a NavigationPage with a back button, instead of switching to the Genres tab. Genre chips have hover effects.</p>
        <p>Dynamic release page tabs — empty tabs (related releases, team, torrents) are hidden automatically instead of showing blank placeholders. Tabs appear dynamically when async data arrives.</p>
        <p>Visual improvements — smooth CSS hover transitions (200ms ease-out-quad) across flowbox items, sidebar rows, navigation tabs, player buttons, and filter chips. Watch progress bar increased to 4px with accent color for better visibility. Tag cards with centered titles and emoji background blur effects.</p>
        <p>Player stability — fixed player cleanup on navigation back by removing unreliable hiding/unmap signals. Cleanup now fires only via explicit back button, NavigationView pop, and window close. Idempotent cleanup prevents double-stop issues.</p>
        <p>Infrastructure — centralized AniLibria API URLs into a single constants file. Image download limit increased from 10 MB to 30 MB. Tags statistics and clear button added to preferences. Repository moved to alt-gnome organization, project Telegram channel and chat added.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.5.0" date="2026-03-08">
      <description>
        <p>Major update with genres, franchises, tabbed release page, Blueprint UI, accent colors, offline mode, and full Russian translation.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.1.0" date="2026-03-07">
      <description>
        <p>Initial release with catalog, search, and video player.</p>
      </description>
    </release>
  </releases>
</component>
